Day 2 of Zeroes to Heroes Challenge
Task 1- identify the given number is even or odd ->
          to identify whether the number enterd is even or odd.The program takes an input of an integer.
          Then it scan that the entered number is completly divisible or not.If the entered number is completly divisible then it prints yes the entered number is even.
          If the entered number is not divisible by 2 then it prints "The entered number is odd"
Task 2- To identify wheter the person is eligible to voote or not ->
          To identify the person is eligible to vote or not the program asks the person makw an input of an integer that would be the age of the person.
          Then it checks than the age of person is greater or equal to 18 or not.
          If the age of person is greater or equal to 18 then it prints/says than "Yes you are eligible to vote"
          ELse it print/syas "You are not eligible to vote right now"
Task 3 - To check which number is greater ->
         To check which number is greater the program takes two inputs "Xand Y" where X will be first number and Y will be second number.
         Then it identify that X>Y or X<Y.
         If X>Y the program prints "first number is greater than second number".
         If X<Y the program prints "second number is greater than first number".
